column5: In this months infisherman a monster muskie was caught in GreenBay Wisconsin by Brett Alexander (alexansersportfishing.com) measuring 57.5 inches and sporting a 33.5 inch girth picture in the magazine this particular fishery carries great lakes strain muskies which grow big and fast in GreenBay
That's a giant.  Interesting that its exactly 0.5 inches longer and fatter than the last "biggest live-release fish".

That was the first thought that came to me as well, the pic is in infisherman have a look havnt heard anything else on this fish where as McNairs fish was all over the news, other fishing boards etc in no time
Man, I can't believe how fat that thing must be.
Only fitting that GB gets that video back up in this post...  Just so much suspicion and question in the Muskie world... it's just another fish!

Muskyhunter has a better understanding of humor though Wayne....  www.xtranormal.com/watch/7738905/   add ' http:// ' to it. Hopefully it was something someone else said in the post that made it go away. I was crying after watching it.
